  "text": "(the natural extension of (8)). Now replacing x in (12) by its noisy observation y, one obtains (4) with β = ±1, T ∈ D t 0 , n ∈ N, and κ, μ ∈] − 1, +∞[. Let us emphasis that these estimators were originally introduced in [CITATION_1] with κ, μ ∈ N and since they are obtained by taking the first term in the Jacobi series expansion, we call them minimal Jacobi estimators. Hence, it is natural to extend these two parameters from N to ] − 1, +∞[.",
